cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper deals with learning representations of motion from unlabeled video, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a model based on deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of motion information for localization, tracking, and odometry, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to representing motion based on group properties, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
